Anyone have advice on debugging inference failures?
```julia&gt; @code_warntype vload(ptr, i, False())
Variables
  #self#::Core.Const(VectorizationBase.vload)
  ptr::VectorizationBase.StridedPointer{Float64, 1, 1, 0, (1,), Tuple{StaticInt{8}}, Tuple{StaticInt{1}}}
  i::Tuple{MM{32, 1, Int64}}
  A::Core.Const(False())

Body::Union{VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, _B, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, _B} where _B, VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, _B, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, _B} where _B, VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, _B, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, _B} where _B, VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, T, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, T} where T} where _A
1 ─      nothing
│   %2 = VectorizationBase.pointer(ptr)::Ptr{Float64}
│   %3 = VectorizationBase.linear_index(ptr, i)::VectorizationBase.LazyMulAdd{8, 0, MM{32, 1, Int64}}
│   %4 = VectorizationBase.vload(%2, %3, A)::Union{VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, _B, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, _B} where _B, VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, _B, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, _B} where _B, VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, _B, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, _B} where _B, VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, _A, T, _C} where _C&lt;:VectorizationBase.AbstractSIMDVector{_A, T} where T} where _A
└──      return %4

julia&gt; p = pointer(ptr); li = VectorizationBase.linear_index(ptr, i);

julia&gt; @code_warntype vload(p, li, False())
Variables
  #self#::Core.Const(VectorizationBase.vload)
  ptr::Ptr{Float64}
  i::VectorizationBase.LazyMulAdd{8, 0, MM{32, 1, Int64}}
  A::Core.Const(False())

Body::VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, 8, Float64, Vec{8, Float64}}
1 ─      nothing
│   %2 = VectorizationBase.register_size()::Core.Const(static(64))
│   %3 = VectorizationBase._vload(ptr, i, A, %2)::VectorizationBase.VecUnroll{3, 8, Float64, Vec{8, Float64}}
└──      return %3```
The call `VectorizationBase.vload(%2, %3, A)` isn't inferred even though all three arguments are.
Yet, when I call that method directly, inference succeeds.

Anyone know why inference can fail like this? And when it does, what sort of changes can make it succeed?

